# Analysis of Inflation Trends in Nigeria and Their Impact on Household Purchasing Power (2020–2026)

## Overview
Inflation has become one of the biggest economic challenges facing Nigerians. As prices of food, transportation, housing, and healthcare rise, many households struggle to maintain their standard of living.

This project analyzes Nigeria’s inflation trends from 2020 to 2026 using Microsoft Excel. It examines how rising prices have affected household purchasing power and consumer spending patterns.

## Project Objectives
- Analyze inflation trends in Nigeria from 2020 to 2026
- Identify periods of significant inflation increases  
- Examine the impact of inflation on household purchasing power
- Present findings using pivot tables, charts, and dashboards
- Provide data-driven recommendations

## Tools Used
- **Microsoft Excel**: Data Cleaning, Pivot Tables, Pivot Charts, Data Visualization

## Methodology
**Data Cleaning**: Removed duplicates, handled missing values, corrected inconsistencies, and formatted the dataset.  
**Data Analysis**: Used Pivot Tables to summarize yearly inflation patterns and created charts to visualize trends.

## Key Findings
- Inflation generally increased between 2020 and 2026
- Food prices experienced the highest increases
- Rising transportation costs drove up living expenses
- Household purchasing power declined significantly
- Families adjusted by reducing discretionary spending

## Conclusion
Inflation has had a substantial impact on Nigerian households. As prices rise, many families struggle to afford basic necessities. Monitoring these trends helps policymakers, businesses, and individuals make informed financial decisions.

## Recommendations
1. Strengthen policies aimed at reducing inflation
2. Support local agricultural production to lower food prices  
3. Improve transportation infrastructure to reduce logistics costs
4. Encourage better household budgeting and savings practices
